{
  "texts": [
    "We instruct a large language model (LLM) to conduct the final verification using the prompt defined in Appendix E.4.",
    "The OECD provides a wealth of trustworthy, observational data on a diverse set of statistics which serve as a strong focal point to explore a wider range of semantic frames.",
    "For example, there are statistics related to health (including healthcare coverage, health risk factors, pharmaceutical markets, etc.",
    "), financial information (including pension assets, stocks and investments, employment earnings, unemployment rates, etc.",
    "), scientific data (air pollution, greenhouse gas emissions, exposure to droughts/floods/wildfires, energy consumption, plastic leakage, etc."
  ]
}